<Content>over-rated As this Hotel is a 4 star, i was expecting just a little bit better than average. The reception staff were polite and friendly enough, but the rooms were in need of a refurbish. Breakfast was in a tiny room not big enough for all the guest that were staying, and the staff did'nt seem to know what they were doing. Everything was a little bit tired, shower head kept falling off the wall and spinning all around the bathroom, soaking everything in sight, towells were almost see through, no soap or other accessories. I have found better in 2 star hotels. The location is not in the least bit handy. It says 10mins from the main shopping area, but 1 hour later we finally hit the main shops (Zara). Overall not good value for money, but as a 2.5 or at most 3 star it would be fine. 
