<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>A Little Gem Stayed at Century Park 5th to 8th April 2005 with my wife and 12 year old son. Had Free child and Free breakfast deal - excellent, no hidden problems. Lovely clean hotel, just refurbished, a bit basic but very comfortable and friendly. On a busy road so expect some noise at the front, but not too bad at night. Rooms are on the small side but well equipped with aircon, TV, mini bar, safe, hairdryer, and good marble bathroom. You have to walk 3 or 4 blocks (10 Minutes max) to Metro but the area seems safe - we had no problems even at night. Bus stops very close to hotel, the 41 takes you to Las Ramblas, Port Olympic, the zoo etc so very convenient. Breakfast is great, cold buffet but lots of choice of cereals, meats, cheese, pastries and cakes, and it's free. Well worth considering this hotel if you are on a budget. The staff are really helpful and speak good english. Try the Hotelclub website Last Minute Deals for the best price. We did and no complaints. Enjoy your trip and make sure you ride the cable cars across the harbour - great fun. 
