<Author>Lukehead
<Content>Safe, quiet, clean Don't let the forst reviewer put you off!Small hotel in a residential area. View is of three small apartment buildings, one Art Deco, one Art Nouveau, one modern, across the street - charming and you can peek in the windows. Hotel is currently being renovated so there is some noise but not enough to interfere with a pleasant stay. Small but well arragnged room. Again, another great Spanish marble bathroom with big towels and good water pressure.There was a growing wet spot in the carpeting, under the window desk counter that gave the room a slightly mouldy smell. We credited it to the renovation work and constant rain of the last week because the room was immacuately clean otherwise. We reported it to the front desk and they seemed surprised and concerned. When we returned that evening, while it was still there, it was apparant they had been working on correcting.Small breakfast rooms ( temporary I think during renovation) but very nice/ample seelction of breads, pastries, juice, fresh fruit, coffees/tea, yoghurt, cheese, meats and wonderful sesame seed whole wheat rolls.Metro stops 3/4 blocks in any direction.Barcelona is a beautiful city! 
